credit.credit-words: Every care, and every sorrow, Be it great, or be it small, Yesterday, to-day, to-morrow, When, where'er it may befall, Lay we humbly at Thy feet, Suppliants at Thy mercy-seat.
Still the weary, sick, and dying Need a brother's, sister's care, On Thy higher help relying May we now their burdens share, Bringing all our offerings meet Suppliants at Thy mercy seat.
Thou to whom the sick and dying
So may sickness, sin, and sadness To Thy healing virtue yield, Till the sick and sad, in gladness, Rescued, ransomed, cleans√®d, healed, One in Thee together meet, Pardoned at Thy judgment seat.
